msgid "Install the app"
msgstr "Install the app"

msgid ""
"Build and deploy the CHAT app to your DHIS2 instance, or install it "
"directly from the DHIS2 App Hub if it is listed there."
msgstr ""
"Build and deploy the CHAT app to your DHIS2 instance, or install it "
"directly from the DHIS2 App Hub if it is listed there."

msgid "The app requires DHIS2 version 2.41 or higher."
msgstr "The app requires DHIS2 version 2.41 or higher."

msgid ""
"After installation the app appears in the DHIS2 app menu under its "
"registered display name."
msgstr ""
"After installation the app appears in the DHIS2 app menu under its "
"registered display name."

msgid "Assign user authorities"
msgstr "Assign user authorities"

msgid ""
"CHAT uses a custom authority to control who can manage assessments. Assign "
"it to the relevant user roles in DHIS2 → User Management → User Roles."
msgstr ""
"CHAT uses a custom authority to control who can manage assessments. Assign "
"it to the relevant user roles in DHIS2 → User Management → User Roles."

msgid ""
"Open the target user role, go to the Authorities tab, search for the "
"authority below, and save."
msgstr ""
"Open the target user role, go to the Authorities tab, search for the "
"authority below, and save."

msgid ""
"Users without this authority can still access Data Capture and Guides, but "
"cannot create or delete assessments."
msgstr ""
"Users without this authority can still access Data Capture and Guides, but "
"cannot create or delete assessments."

msgid "Create, import, link, and delete assessments in the Settings page"
msgstr "Create, import, link, and delete assessments in the Settings page"

msgid "Import a metadata package"
msgstr "Import a metadata package"

msgid ""
"Assessment tools are distributed as DHIS2 metadata JSON packages. Download "
"a package and use the import wizard to push it to your instance."
msgstr ""
"Assessment tools are distributed as DHIS2 metadata JSON packages. Download "
"a package and use the import wizard to push it to your instance."

msgid "Navigate to Settings → New assessment and upload the metadata .json file."
msgstr "Navigate to Settings → New assessment and upload the metadata .json file."

msgid ""
"Review the detected program, sections, data elements, option sets, and "
"indicators."
msgstr ""
"Review the detected program, sections, data elements, option sets, and "
"indicators."

msgid ""
"Assign the relevant organisation units, then click Import assessment to "
"push the metadata to DHIS2 and register the record."
msgstr ""
"Assign the relevant organisation units, then click Import assessment to "
"push the metadata to DHIS2 and register the record."

msgid ""
"Pre-built metadata packages are available in the meta-data-packages folder "
"of the repository."
msgstr ""
"Pre-built metadata packages are available in the meta-data-packages folder "
"of the repository."

msgid "Link an existing program (optional)"
msgstr "Link an existing program (optional)"

msgid ""
"If the DHIS2 program is already deployed in your instance, you can register "
"it without re-importing the metadata."
msgstr ""
"If the DHIS2 program is already deployed in your instance, you can register "
"it without re-importing the metadata."

msgid "Navigate to Settings → Link existing program."
msgstr "Navigate to Settings → Link existing program."

msgid ""
"Search for the program by name, then click Add to register it as a CHAT "
"assessment."
msgstr ""
"Search for the program by name, then click Add to register it as a CHAT "
"assessment."

msgid ""
"The program must already exist in DHIS2 — this step only adds the local "
"assessment record."
msgstr ""
"The program must already exist in DHIS2 — this step only adds the local "
"assessment record."

msgid "Verify the setup"
msgstr "Verify the setup"

msgid ""
"After adding an assessment, confirm it is visible and working for both "
"admin and data-capture users."
msgstr ""
"After adding an assessment, confirm it is visible and working for both "
"admin and data-capture users."

msgid "Open Settings and confirm the new assessment appears with status Active."
msgstr "Open Settings and confirm the new assessment appears with status Active."

msgid ""
"Open an assessment record and check that all form sections and data "
"elements load correctly."
msgstr ""
"Open an assessment record and check that all form sections and data "
"elements load correctly."

msgid "Guide"
msgstr "Guide"

msgid "Quick links"
msgstr "Quick links"

msgid "Before you start"
msgstr "Before you start"

msgid "Browse metadata packages →"
msgstr "Browse metadata packages →"

msgid "Open assessment settings"
msgstr "Open assessment settings"

msgid ""
"Start from Settings if you need to create or import a new assessment. This "
"area is intended for users who have the required chat settings authority."
msgstr ""
"Start from Settings if you need to create or import a new assessment. This "
"area is intended for users who have the required chat settings authority."

msgid "Use the New assessment action to open the import flow."
msgstr "Use the New assessment action to open the import flow."

msgid ""
"Existing assessments stay visible in the settings list for review or "
"cleanup."
msgstr ""
"Existing assessments stay visible in the settings list for review or "
"cleanup."

msgid "Load the metadata JSON"
msgstr "Load the metadata JSON"

msgid ""
"Upload the DHIS2 metadata JSON file for the assessment tool. The import "
"flow checks the file before it lets you continue."
msgstr ""
"Upload the DHIS2 metadata JSON file for the assessment tool. The import "
"flow checks the file before it lets you continue."

msgid "Only `.json` files are accepted in the import step."
msgstr "Only `.json` files are accepted in the import step."

msgid "Parsing warnings are shown before you import the assessment."
msgstr "Parsing warnings are shown before you import the assessment."

msgid "Review the detected program"
msgstr "Review the detected program"

msgid ""
"Use the review step to inspect the program, program stage, sections, data "
"elements, option sets, and indicators that were found in the JSON."
msgstr ""
"Use the review step to inspect the program, program stage, sections, data "
"elements, option sets, and indicators that were found in the JSON."

msgid "Use the Next button after you finish reviewing the metadata preview."
msgstr "Use the Next button after you finish reviewing the metadata preview."

msgid ""
"The preview step helps you catch missing or unexpected metadata before "
"import."
msgstr ""
"The preview step helps you catch missing or unexpected metadata before "
"import."

msgid "Assign organisation units"
msgstr "Assign organisation units"

msgid ""
"The next step asks you to select organisation units before the final import "
"action becomes available."
msgstr ""
"The next step asks you to select organisation units before the final import "
"action becomes available."

msgid "You must select at least one organisation unit before importing."
msgstr "You must select at least one organisation unit before importing."

msgid ""
"This selection is part of the guided import flow and is confirmed before "
"the final import action."
msgstr ""
"This selection is part of the guided import flow and is confirmed before "
"the final import action."

msgid "Import the assessment"
msgstr "Import the assessment"

msgid ""
"Use Import assessment to save the program to DHIS2 and then register the "
"local assessment record so it appears in the chat app."
msgstr ""
"Use Import assessment to save the program to DHIS2 and then register the "
"local assessment record so it appears in the chat app."

msgid ""
"If the DHIS2 save succeeds but the local save fails, the screen shows a "
"retry option for the local record."
msgstr ""
"If the DHIS2 save succeeds but the local save fails, the screen shows a "
"retry option for the local record."

msgid "After a successful import, the app returns you to the settings list."
msgstr "After a successful import, the app returns you to the settings list."

msgid "Confirm the assessment is available"
msgstr "Confirm the assessment is available"

msgid ""
"After import, check the settings list and then open Data Capture to confirm "
"the new active assessment is available for users."
msgstr ""
"After import, check the settings list and then open Data Capture to confirm "
"the new active assessment is available for users."

msgid "Active assessments appear in the data capture home screen."
msgstr "Active assessments appear in the data capture home screen."

msgid ""
"Use the assessment details view in settings if you need to inspect the "
"imported program metadata."
msgstr ""
"Use the assessment details view in settings if you need to inspect the "
"imported program metadata."

